parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The seat belt latch breaks or falls apart
the seat belt becomes stuck or jammed
the seat belt buckle releases unexpectedly
the seat belt fails to lock in
the seat belt handle breaks
the seat belt retractor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration while braking can cause loss of control or accidents, especially on wet pavement or when driving on back roads.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes while braking
the vehicle vibrates while braking
the brakes feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or refuse to shift gears, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates

the transmission fails to engage or disengage properly.
